.SH NAME
SDL_SetGamepadLED \- Update a gamepad's LED color\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_gamepad\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "bool SDL_SetGamepadLED(SDL_Gamepad *gamepad, Uint8 red, Uint8 green, Uint8 blue);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
An example of a joystick LED is the light on the back of a PlayStation 4's
DualShock 4 controller\[char46]

For gamepads with a single color LED, the maximum of the RGB values will be
used as the LED brightness\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I gamepad
the gamepad to update\[char46]
.TP
.I red
the intensity of the red LED\[char46]
.TP
.I green
the intensity of the green LED\[char46]
.TP
.I blue
the intensity of the blue LED\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns true on success or false on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

